{"title_page": "Fantastica Mania 2018", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese/Mexican professional wrestling show series}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestling event\n|name = ''Fantastica Mania'' 2018\n|image = Fantastica Mania 2018.jpg\n|caption = 2018 poster showing both CMLL and NJPW competitors on the tour\n|promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]]<br />[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]\n|date = {{Unbulleted list|January 12, 2018<ref name=Jan12/>|January 14, 2018<ref name=Jan14/>|January 15, 2018<ref name=Jan15/>|January 16, 2018<ref name=Jan16/>|January 17, 2018<ref name=Jan17/>|January 19, 2018<ref name=Jan19/>|January 21, 2018<ref name=Jan21/>|January 22, 2018<ref name=Jan22/>}}\n|attendance =1554 (Jan 12)<ref name=Jan12/><br>\n|venue =\n|city ={{Unbulleted list|[[Nagoya]]<ref name=Jan12/>|[[Kyoto]]<ref name=Jan14/>|[[Takamatsu, Kagawa|Takamatsu]]<ref name=Jan15/>|[[Osaka]]<ref name=Jan16/>|[[Toyama, Toyama|Toyama]]<ref name=Jan17/>|[[Tokyo]]<ref name=Jan19/><ref name=Jan21/><ref name=Jan22/>}}\n|liveevent=Y\n|lastevent=[[Fantastica Mania 2017|2017]]\n|nextevent=[[Fantastica Mania 2019|2019]]\n|event=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] event\n|lastevent2=[[Sin Piedad (2018)|Sin Piedad]]\n|nextevent2=[[CMLL Torneo Nacional de Parejas Incre\u00edbles (2018)|Torneo Nacional de Parejas Incre\u00edbles]]\n|event2=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] event\n|lastevent3=[[New Year Dash!!]]\n|nextevent3=Road to the New Beginning\n}}\n'''''Fantastica Mania'' 2018''' was a [[professional wrestling]] tour, co-produced by the Japanese [[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] (NJPW) [[Professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] and the Mexican [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] (CMLL) promotion. The tour took place between January 12 and 22, 2018, with shows taking place in [[Nagoya]], [[Kyoto]], [[Takamatsu, Kagawa|Takamatsu]], [[Osaka]], [[Toyama, Toyama|Toyama]] and [[Tokyo]], Japan. The 2018 tour was the eight time that NJPW and CMLL co-promoted shows in Japan under the ''[[Fantastica Mania]]'' name. With eight shows, the 2018 tour was the longest in ''Fantastica Mania'' history. The shows geneally featured seven matches each night, with several shows being shown at least in part on SamuraiTV, and the last three shows were shown in full as part of the [[NJPW World]] streaming content.\n\nThe eight shows featured a total of 66 matches, four of which for CMLL championships including [[Soberano Jr.]], [[Niebla Roja]] and [[Volador Jr.]] successfully defending their championships, and [[El Cuatrero]] defeating [[\u00c1ngel de Oro]] to win the [[CMLL World Middleweight Championship]]. The focal point of the last two show was the \"CMLL Brothers tag team tournament, won by [[Gran Guerrero]] and [[\u00daltimo Guerrero]], that also included El Cuatrero/[[Sans\u00f3n (wrestler)|Sans\u00f3n]], \u00c1ngel de Oro/Niebla Roja, and [[Dragon Lee (wrestler)|Dragon Lee]]/[[M\u00edstico II|M\u00edstico]].\n\n==Background==\nThe 2018 ''[[Fantastica Mania]]'' tour was the eight year in a row where Japanese wrestling promotion [[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] (NJPW) promoted a series of shows with their Mexican partner promotion [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] (CMLL). Due to the co-promotional nature of the shows, they rarely feature any development in ongoing NJPW or CMLL storylines, instead of focusing on inter-promotional matches. [[Negro Casas]] had originally been announced as a participant, but he was injured during a match against [[Sam Adonis]] as CMLLs [[Sin Piedad (2018)|Sin Piedad]] event on January 1.<ref name=SP2018Ovaciones>{{cite web | url=https://ovaciones.com/cobra-venganza-2/ | title=\u00a1Cobra venganza! | date=January 2, 2018 | accessdate=September 21, 2018 | first=Arturo | last=Rosas Plata | work=Ovaciones | language=Spanish | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180923200744/https://ovaciones.com/cobra-venganza-2/ | archive-date=September 23, 2018 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=SP2018Esto>{{cite web | url=https://www.esto.com.mx/325308-noticias-lucha-libre-negro-casa-vs-sam-adonis-cabellera-vs-cabellera-negro-casas-arranca-el-ano-rapando-a-sam-adonis/ | title=Negro Casas arranca el a\u00f1o rapando a Sam Adons | date=January 2, 2018 | accessdate=September 21, 2018 | work=Esto | language=Spanish | first=Roberto | last=Quezada Monter}}</ref> NJPW main-stay [[Rocky Romero]] took Casas' place on the tour.\n{{clear}}\n\n==Results==\n===January 12===\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref name=Jan12>{{cite web | url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/tornament/116500?showResult=1 | title=NJPW PRESENTS CMLL FANTASTICA MANIA 2018 | publisher=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] | language=Japanese | accessdate=October 28, 2018 | date=January 12, 2018 }}</ref>\n|hide=all\n\n|stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Variations of singles matches|Singles match]]\n|match1=[[Drone (wrestler)|Drone]] defeated [[Disturbio]]\n|time1=06:53\n\n|stip2=[[Tag Team]] match\n|match2=[[Shigeo Okumura|Okumura]] and [[Puma King|Puma]] (with [[Mima Shimoda]]) defeated [[Fuego (wrestler)|Fuego]] and [[Star Jr.]]\n|time2=09:44\n\n|stip3=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple men teamed matches|Eight-man tag team match]]\n|match3=[[Chaos (professional wrestling)|Chaos]] ([[Rocky Romero]], [[Sho Tanaka|SHO]] and [[Yohei Komatsu|YOH]]) and [[El Cuatrero]] defeated [[\u00c1ngel de Oro]], [[Jushin Thunder Liger]], [[Ryusuke Taguchi]] and [[Tiger Mask IV|Tiger Mask]]\n|time3=09:41\n\n|stip4=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple men teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]]\n|match4=[[Soberano Jr.]], [[Niebla Roja]] and [[Volador Jr.]] defeated [[B\u00e1rbaro Cavernario]], [[Gran Guerrero]] and [[Sans\u00f3n (wrestler)|Sans\u00f3n]]\n|time4=09:26\n\n|stip5=Eight-man tag team match\n|match5=[[Los Ingobernables de Japon]] ([[Tetsuya Bushi|BUSHI]], [[Hiromu Takahashi]] and [[Tetsuya Naito]]) and [[Rush (wrestler)|Rush]] defeated [[Dragon Lee (wrestler)|Dragon Lee]], [[Hirai Kawato]], [[Kushida (wrestler)|KUSHIDA]] and [[S